physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Fetal biparietal diameter (BPD) 54 mm (< P10, -1.85 SD); head circumference (HC) 204 mm (< P10, -1.53 SD); abdominal circumference (AC) 177 mm (< P10, -1.55 SD); femur length (FL) 39 mm (P15.4, -1.02 SD); cystic structures detected at the posterior horn of the lateral ventricles; single umbilical artery (SUA).
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Follow-up ultrasound at 28+1 weeks showed persistent cystic structures at the posterior horn of each lateral ventricle, which had increased in size. Fetal growth trend slower than normal, with BPD 63 mm (< P1, -2.64 SD), HC 232 mm (< P1, -2.99 SD), AC 205 mm (< P1, -2.56 SD), and FL 46 mm (< P3, -1.94 SD).

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Mild dilation of the bilateral ventricles; cystic structures around them; abnormal signal foci in the white matter of the fetal right parietal lobe; smaller brain diameter and sulcus development.
